tournament.name: MTG SEA Championship Final Season 2 Round 3

decks.notes: This Golgari Aggro deck focuses on quickly overwhelming the opponent with aggressive creatures and disruptive spells. The deck includes powerful cards like Liliana of the Veil, Archfiend of the Dross, and Glissa Sunslayer, while also utilizing removal spells like Go for the Throat and Cut Down to control the opponent's board. With a mix of creature power and disruption, this deck aims to apply pressure early and maintain board advantage throughout the game to secure a quick victory.

This deck focuses on aggression and taking advantage of the opponent's weaknesses by controlling the board with a mix of creatures and spells. The deck includes a variety of evasion abilities, disruptive cards, and a few powerful finishers to quickly overwhelm the opponent. By combining aggressive creatures like Spyglass Siren and Faerie Mastermind with control elements like Go for the Throat and Liliana of the Veil, the deck aims to apply constant pressure and force the opponent into making unfavorable trades. The key strategy is to maintain a balance between aggression and disruption to secure victory.

This Boros Aggro deck focuses on quickly building a wide board of creatures and overwhelming the opponent with aggression. The key strategy is to efficiently flood the board with low-cost creatures like Novice Inspector and Knight-Errant of Eos, supported by resilient threats like Warden of the Inner Sky and Voldaren Epicure. The deck also includes disruptive elements like Imodane's Recruiter and Resolute Reinforcements to apply pressure and maintain board control. With a mix of efficient creatures and powerful spells, this deck aims to close out games quickly through combat damage.

This UW Control deck focuses on card advantage, disruption, and controlling the board through counterspells and removal. The deck aims to outvalue the opponent by utilizing cards like Tishana's Tidebinder, Memory Deluge, and Deduce to draw cards and maintain control. It also disrupts the opponent's strategy with cards like Get Lost and March of Otherworldly Light. The deck utilizes a variety of lands to fix mana and provide utility, while also including win conditions like The Wandering Emperor and Jace, the Perfected Mind to close out the game.

This deck focuses on playing aggressively with a mix of creatures, spells, and lands that work together to put pressure on the opponent quickly. The key strategy involves using powerful creatures like Slogurk, the Overslime and Rona, Herald of Invasion alongside removal spells like Go for the Throat to control the board and deal damage efficiently. The deck also includes support cards like Relic of Legends and Xander's Lounge to help maintain card advantage and support the aggressive game plan. Additionally, the mana base is carefully constructed to ensure smooth and consistent gameplay.

The main focus of this deck is to control the game by using various removal spells and counterspells to disrupt your opponent's strategy. The deck also includes card draw and recursion effects to ensure you have the resources you need to outlast your opponent. With a mix of efficient removal, counterspells, and card advantage, the deck aims to control the game until you can take over with powerful threats like Aclazotz, Deepest Betrayal and Jace, the Perfected Mind.

The deck focuses on utilizing control elements to manage the board and opponent's resources effectively. It includes a mix of creatures with powerful abilities, removal spells, and land cards to support the strategy. By controlling the game state and gradually building up resources, the deck aims to overwhelm the opponent and secure victory. Additionally, it features cards that provide card advantage and protection to maintain its position in the game. The deck is designed to handle various types of threats and maintain control over the course of the match.

This Orzhov Control deck focuses on managing the opponent's resources while building up your own advantage through card advantage and removal spells. The strategy involves disrupting the opponent's game plan with removal spells like Go for the Throat and Sheoldred's Edict, while gaining card advantage with Phyrexian Arena and Liliana of the Veil. The deck also utilizes creatures like Doorkeeper Thrull and Hunted Bonebrute to control the board. The deck aims to outvalue the opponent by grinding out incremental advantages and ultimately overwhelming them with powerful threats like Sheoldred, the Apocalypse and Aclazotz, Deepest Betrayal.

The main concept of this Golgari Aggro deck is to quickly establish board control and pressure the opponent with aggressive creatures and removal spells. The deck focuses on disrupting the opponent's strategy with cards like Duress and Go for the Throat, while also deploying powerful threats like Glissa Sunslayer and Sheoldred, the Apocalypse to close out the game. By combining efficient removal and resilient creatures, the deck aims to overwhelm the opponent and secure a swift victory before they can stabilize.

This deck focuses on quickly building a board presence and overwhelming the opponent with aggressive creatures. It includes cards that can surprise the opponent and disrupt their strategy, along with powerful creatures that can deal massive damage. The mana base is designed to ensure consistent access to all necessary colors of mana. The goal is to establish dominance early in the game and maintain pressure until the opponent is unable to recover. The key strategy is to outpace the opponent and close out the game before they have a chance to stabilize.

This deck focuses on quickly playing multiple low-cost creatures and using pump spells to increase their power, allowing for fast and aggressive attacks. The goal is to overwhelm the opponent with a flurry of creatures and damage output, while also having some protection spells to keep key creatures safe. The deck includes a mix of creatures with haste and abilities that synergize well with pump spells, creating a solid aggro strategy that aims to finish the game before the opponent can set up their own game plan.

This deck focuses on managing resources and controlling the game through a combination of powerful creatures and spells. It utilizes a mix of card draw, removal, and counter spells to outlast opponents and set up game-winning plays. The key strategy is to stabilize the board with efficient threats like Nissa, Resurgent Animist and Aftermath Analyst, while disrupting the opponent's game plan with cards like Ill-Timed Explosion and Memory Deluge. By carefully managing resources and reacting to the opponent's threats, the deck aims to grind out a victory through superior card advantage and board control.
